description: This module is used to configure AnalyticsProfile object

hs_event_throttle_window.description: Time window (in secs) within which only unique health change events should occur.

apdex_rtt_tolerated_factor.description: Tolerated client to avi round trip time(rtt) factor.

disable_se_analytics.description: Disable node (service engine) level analytics forvs metrics.

conn_server_lossy_timeo_rexmt_threshold.description: A connection between avi and server is considered lossy when more than this percentage of packets are retransmitted due to timeout.

apdex_server_rtt_tolerated_factor.description: Tolerated client to avi round trip time(rtt) factor.

hs_security_tls12_score.description: Score assigned when supporting tls1.2 encryption protocol.

exclude_server_tcp_reset_as_error.description: Exclude server tcp reset from errors.

hs_min_dos_rate.description: Dos connection rate below which the dos security assessment will not kick in.

exclude_no_dns_record_as_error.description: Exclude queries to domains that did not have configured services/records from the list of errors.

conn_server_lossy_zero_win_size_event_th.description: A server connection is considered lossy when percentage of times a packet could not be trasmitted due to tcp zero window is above this threshold.

hs_max_resources_penalty.description: Maximum penalty that may be deducted from health score for high resource utilization.

conn_lossy_total_rexmt_threshold.description: A connection between client and avi is considered lossy when more than this percentage of packets are retransmitted.

client_log_streaming_config.description: Configure to stream logs to an external server.

hs_pscore_traffic_threshold_l4_client.description: Threshold number of connections in 5min, below which apdexr, apdexc, rum_apdex, and other network quality metrics are not computed.

hs_security_weak_signature_algo_penalty.description: Penalty for allowing weak signature algorithm(s).

exclude_no_valid_gs_member_as_error.description: Exclude queries to gslb services that have no available members from the list of errors.

apdex_server_response_threshold.description: A server http response is considered satisfied if latency is less than the satisfactory latency threshold.

hs_security_cipherscore_ge128b.description: Score assigned when the minimum cipher strength is greater than equal to 128 bits.

resp_code_block.description: Block of http response codes to be excluded from being classified as an error.

hs_performance_boost.description: Adds free performance score credits to health score.

exclude_invalid_dns_domain_as_error.description: Exclude dns queries to domains outside the domains configured in the dns application profile from the list of errors.

exclude_http_error_codes.description: List of http status codes to be excluded from being classified as an error.

hs_max_anomaly_penalty.description: Maximum penalty that may be deducted from health score for anomalies.

hs_security_tls11_score.description: Score assigned when supporting tls1.1 encryption protocol.

apdex_rum_tolerated_factor.description: Virtual service threshold factor for tolerated page load time (plt) as multiple of apdex_rum_threshold.

exclude_gs_down_as_error.description: Exclude queries to gslb services that are operationally down from the list of errors.

state.description: The state that should be applied on the entity.

conn_server_lossy_ooo_threshold.description: A connection between avi and server is considered lossy when more than this percentage of out of order packets are received.

exclude_client_close_before_request_as_e.description: Exclude client closed connection before an http request could be completed from being classified as an error.

exclude_persistence_change_as_error.description: Exclude persistence server changed while load balancing' from the list of errors.

conn_server_lossy_total_rexmt_threshold.description: A connection between avi and server is considered lossy when more than this percentage of packets are retransmitted.

conn_lossy_timeo_rexmt_threshold.description: A connection between client and avi is considered lossy when more than this percentage of packets are retransmitted due to timeout.

api_version.description: Avi API version of to use for Avi API and objects.

username.description: Username used for accessing Avi controller. The default value is the environment variable C(AVI_USERNAME).

hs_security_certscore_gt30d.description: Score assigned when the certificate expires in more than 30 days.

description.description: User defined description for the object.

hs_security_ssl30_score.description: Score assigned when supporting ssl3.0 encryption protocol.

client_log_config.description: Configure which logs are sent to the avi controller from ses and how they are processed.

hs_security_cipherscore_eq000b.description: Score assigned when the minimum cipher strength is 0 bits.

hs_security_certscore_le30d.description: Score assigned when the certificate expires in less than or equal to 30 days.

exclude_syn_retransmit_as_error.description: Exclude 'server unanswered syns' from the list of errors.

ranges.description: List of http status code ranges to be excluded from being classified as an error.

controller.description: IP address or hostname of the controller. The default value is the environment variable C(AVI_CONTROLLER).

apdex_server_rtt_threshold.description: Satisfactory client to avi round trip time(rtt).

exclude_server_dns_error_as_error.description: Exclude server dns error response from the list of errors.

hs_security_encalgo_score_rc4.description: Score assigned when rc4 algorithm is used for encryption.

password.description: Password of Avi user in Avi controller. The default value is the environment variable C(AVI_PASSWORD).

hs_security_encalgo_score_none.description: Score assigned when no algorithm is used for encryption.

tenant.description: Name of tenant used for all Avi API calls and context of object.

conn_lossy_zero_win_size_event_threshold.description: A client connection is considered lossy when percentage of times a packet could not be trasmitted due to tcp zero window is above this threshold.

apdex_rum_threshold.description: If a client is able to load a page in less than the satisfactory latency threshold, the pageload is considered satisfied.

hs_pscore_traffic_threshold_l4_server.description: Threshold number of connections in 5min, below which apdexr, apdexc, rum_apdex, and other network quality metrics are not computed.

name.description: The name of the analytics profile.

hs_max_security_penalty.description: Maximum penalty that may be deducted from health score based on security assessment.

apdex_rtt_threshold.description: Satisfactory client to avi round trip time(rtt).

tenant_ref.description: It is a reference to an object of type tenant.

exclude_tcp_reset_as_error.description: Exclude tcp resets by client from the list of potential errors.

hs_security_chain_invalidity_penalty.description: Penalty for allowing certificates with invalid chain.

exclude_invalid_dns_query_as_error.description: Exclude invalid dns queries from the list of errors.

conn_lossy_ooo_threshold.description: A connection between client and avi is considered lossy when more than this percentage of out of order packets are received.

hs_security_cipherscore_lt128b.description: Score assigned when the minimum cipher strength is less than 128 bits.

exclude_unsupported_dns_query_as_error.description: Exclude unsupported dns queries from the list of errors.

url.description: Avi controller URL of the object.

hs_security_tls10_score.description: Score assigned when supporting tls1.0 encryption protocol.

hs_security_certscore_expired.description: Score assigned when the certificate has expired.

apdex_response_threshold.description: If a client receives an http response in less than the satisfactory latency threshold, the request is considered satisfied.

tenant_uuid.description: UUID of tenant used for all Avi API calls and context of object.

hs_security_certscore_le07d.description: Score assigned when the certificate expires in less than or equal to 7 days.
